data.title: Nan Jiang named Fellow of the American Vacuum Society
data.text: Prof. Nan Jiang has been named a Fellow of American Vacuum Society, which is an honor meant to recognize AVS members who have made sustained and outstanding scientific and technical contributions in areas of interest to the Society. His award will be presented at the AVS 69th International Symposium and Exhibition in Portland, Oregon on November 8, 2023. Nan is one of the youngest AVS Fellows and join the prestigious group which includes two of our senior colleagues, Mike Trenary and Luke Hanley. Congratulations!
